The number of recruits from Ukraine preparing to send to Donbass was named
Official representative of the People's Police of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People's Republic (LPR) Andriy Marochko said that in the winter of 2018-2019 Ukraine will send at least 3 thousand to Donbass. recruits.
According to him, thus Kiev plans to "at least somehow complement the units."
"The reluctance of Ukrainian citizens to serve in the Armed Forces of Ukraine, mass dismissal led to low staffing of units," - said Marochko, quoted by RIA Novosti.
He also did not rule out that the real figures of Ukrainians drafted into the army can be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev launched a so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by the operation of the united forces (OS).
It was assumed that this measure would lead to strengthening the role of Ukrainian security forces in resolving the situation.
In late August 2018, the situation in Donbass escalated due to the murder of DPR leader Alexander Zakharchenko.
The DPR authorities qualified the incident as a terrorist attack.
Several people involved in the explosion were detained during the investigation of the criminal case.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by the Ukrainian special services.
The U.S. authorities forced Mask to leave the post of Chairman of the Board of Tesla
American businessman Ilon Musk will leave the position of Chairman of the Board of Directors of Tesla founded by him at the request of the U.S. authorities.
In order to settle the claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $20 million.
According to CNBC, pre-trial agreement with the agency allows Mask to stay in Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $20mn and leave the position of Chairman of the Board of Directors within 45 days of the agreement and at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed to his place.
It is specified that the agreement should still be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission accused Mask of misleading shareholders with a statement on the availability of sufficient funds to buy back the shares of the company and filed an entrepreneur in court.
We are talking about the publication of the businessman on Twitter, where he announced his desire to buy Tesla shares at $420 per piece, but did not do so.
Following the tweet, the stock rose by almost 11%.
British Foreign Minister compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Minister Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union with the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing the member states of the community.
The diplomat made such a statement at the congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
According to Daily Mail, thus Hunt commented on the difficulties in the Brexit negotiation process.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave it.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from the community into prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who wants to flee the prison," the Minister said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to withdraw from the European Union will only aggravate the crisis, says Gazeta.ru.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that the Brexit negotiations reached a deadlock.
So she commented on the results of the informal EU summit in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 following the results of the referendum.
It is expected that the release of the United Kingdom will take place until April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
In addition, the issue remains open on the Irish border.
