Ilon Mask is forced to leave the post of Tesla Board of Directors
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla founder Ilon Mask settled their dispute on fraud.
It is reported by CNBC News.
According to the TV channel, within the framework of the agreements reached, Maska will have to leave the post of head of the board of directors of Tesla.
At the same time, the Commission allowed Mask to maintain the post of head of Tesla.
As noted, the founder of Tesla will also have to pay an administrative fine of $20 million.
A similar amount will be required with Tesla.
At the same time, the money will be distributed among the affected investors.
In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Ilon Mask is an American entrepreneur, a member of the list of 50 richest people, the planet according to Forbes magazine.
He is the head of the SpaceX space corporation, Neuralink neurotheological company and Tesla electric car developer, as well as the co-founder of Paypal.
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission has previously sued Tesla CEO Ilon Mask due to his tweeting of the company's possible repurchase.
Last month, Mask announced plans to make Tesla a private company and buy all shares on the stock exchange at a fixed price of $420.
The cost of the campaign at $420 was allegedly "due to the importance of this number in the marijuana culture," Bloomberg reported earlier, citing the co-director of the security department of the Commission Stephen Peikin.
At the same time, Ilon Mask subsequently refused to buy back the shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit against him by the US Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman said that he considers the accusations of fraud unfounded, and added that he is very disappointed and saddened by these claims.
"Honesty is the most important value in my life and the facts prove that I have not violated it in any way," the businessman said in an interview with CNBC.
At the same time, in August, a group of Tesla shareholders filed a collective claim against Mask, complaining about the incurred financial losses.
The plaintiffs claimed that the posts of the businessman brought them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that the tweets of the businessman were misleading, which is why the sellers of Tesla shares were forced to purchase paper at artificially inflated prices to cover their positions.
Other claimants also noted that Ilona Mask's careless statements led to sharp fluctuations in the course.
In September, Ilona Maska accused the head of Citron Research, also of stock exchange machinations.
Meanwhile, if Mask could not settle his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission, he would be threatened to be removed from the management of the company and even a prison.
In particular, former Chairman of the Commission Harvey Pitt told CNBC about this.
Mask - "a good guy who does not know how to drive the car company."
