Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational - control work, informatization and provision of information security of the republican department, over the past eight months more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself, more than 42 thousand - section "Data Bank of executive industries," downloaded 661 payment receipt for payment of debts.
According to Chairman of the Public Council of the Federal Security Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Valery Bogdanov, almost every resident of the region are listed debts for utility payments, fines traffic police, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured from unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form, for example, the ban on travel abroad.
That is why the FSB of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends to all who planned a trip abroad, to clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the availability of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service created the "Data Bank of executive industries" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is not only on the regional sites of the FSB of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communications iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information about the executive proceedings initiated by Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains Assistant Head of the FSB of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgaev.
"If there are debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its number, the amount and the form of debt; the address of the bailiffs department; the name of the bailiff-executor; contact telephone.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
